## (Proof)

(i) WLOG, we assume $\nu(E) \in [-\infty, \infty)$ for all $E \in \mathcal{M}$. Let

$$
m = \sup \{\nu(E) : E \text{ is a positive set}\}.
$$

Choose a sequence $\{P_j\}$ of positive sets such that

$$
\lim_{j \to \infty} \nu(P_j) = m.
$$

Let

$$
P = \bigcup_{j=1}^{\infty} P_j.
$$

Then $P$ is a positive set such that $\nu(P) = m$. Note $m &lt; \infty$.

