3.6 Corollary If $f \in L^{1}(\mu)$, then for every $\varepsilon &gt; 0$, there exists $\delta &gt; 0$ such that $|\int_{E} f \, d\mu| &lt; \varepsilon$ whenever $\mu(E) &lt; \delta$.

Proof. Let $\nu$ be defined by

$$
\nu(E) = \int_{E} f \, d\mu.
$$

Apply Theorem 3.5.

Notation. If $\nu(E) = \int_{E} f \, d\mu$ for all $E \in \mathcal{M}$, we write

$$
d\nu = f \, d\mu.
$$

