3.14 Proposition If $\nu_{1}$ and $\nu_{2}$ are complex measures on $(X,\mathcal{M})$, then $|\nu_{1} + \nu_{2}| \leq |\nu_{1}| + |\nu_{2}|$

Proof. Suppose

$$
d v _ {1} = f _ {1} d \mu \text{ and } d v _ {2} = f _ {2} d \mu
$$

(with the same $\mu$). Then,

$$
d \left(v _ {1} + v _ {2}\right) = \left(f _ {1} + f _ {2}\right) d \mu .
$$

Hence

$$
\begin{array}{l}
d | v _ {1} + v _ {2} | = | f _ {1} + f _ {2} | d \mu \\
\leq (| f _ {1} | + | f _ {2} |) d \mu \\
= | f _ {1} | d \mu + | f _ {2} | d \mu \\
= d | v _ {1} | + d | v _ {2} |.
\end{array}
$$

