Definition. For $f \in L_{loc}^{1}$, the Hardy-Littlewood function of $f$ $Hf$ is defined by

$$
(Hf)(x) = \sup_{r &gt; 0} (A_r | f |)(x).
$$

Note that $Hf$ is measurable, since

$$
(Hf)(x) = \sup_{\substack{r &gt; 0 \\ r \in \mathbb{Q}}} (A_r | f |)(x).
$$

