Hence

$$
\begin{array}{l}
m \left(\left\{x: \lim  _ {r \rightarrow 0} \sup  _ {r \rightarrow 0} | A _ {r} f (x) - f (x) | &gt; \alpha \right\}\right) \\
\leq m \left(\left\{x: H (f - g) (x) &gt; \frac {\alpha}{2} \right\}\right) + m \left(\left\{x: | f - g | (x) &gt; \frac {\alpha}{2} \right\}\right) \\
\leq \frac {3 ^ {n}}{\alpha / 2} \int | f - g | d x + \frac {1}{\alpha / 2} \int | f - g | (x) d x \\
&lt;   \frac {3 ^ {n - 1}}{\alpha} \varepsilon + \frac {2}{\alpha} \varepsilon , \quad (\epsilon &gt; 0 \text{ is arbitrary}).
\end{array}
$$

