Definition. A family $\{E_r\}_{r &gt; 0}$ of Borel subsets of $\mathbb{R}^n$ shrink nicely to $x \in \mathbb{R}^n$ if

(i) $E_r \subset B(r, x)$ for each $r$, and
(ii) there is a constant $\alpha &gt; 0$, independent of $r$, such that

$$
m(E_r) &gt; \alpha m(B(r, x)).
$$

