Proof of (4)  $(\Rightarrow)$  Trivial.

$(\Leftarrow)$  Suppose  $f \in L_{loc}^{1}$ . Then, (i) holds. We will show (iii). Let

$E$  be a Borel set,  $\epsilon &gt; 0$ , and  $K_{j} = \{x \in \mathbb{R}^{n} : ||x|| \leq j\}$ .

It suffices to show that there exist open sets  $U_{j}$  such that

$$
\int_ {U _ {j} \backslash (E \cap K _ {j})} f 1 _ {K _ {j}} d m &lt;   \frac {\epsilon}{2 ^ {j}}. \tag {*}
$$

By Corollary 3.6, for every  $\eta &gt;0$ , there is  $\delta &gt;0$  such that

$$
\int_ {A} f 1 _ {K _ {j}} d m &lt;   \eta \quad \text {if} \ m (A) &lt;   \delta .
$$

Thus,  $(\ast)$  follows from the out regularity of the Lebesgue measure.

