Lemma 3.26 If $F \in BV$ is real valued, then $T_F + F$ and $T_F - F$ are increasing.

Proof. If $a = x_0 &lt; \cdots &lt; x_n &lt; b$, then

$$
\sum_{j=1}^{n} |F(x_j) - F(x_{j-1})| \geq F(a) - F(b).
$$

Hence,

$$
T_F(b) - T_F(a) \geq F(b) - F(a).
$$

