# Jordan Decomposition

The representation

$$
F = \frac {1}{2} (T _ {F} + F) - \frac {1}{2} (T _ {F} - F)
$$

of a real-valued  $F \in BV$  is called the Jordan decomposition of  $F$ , and  $\frac{1}{2} (T_F + F)$  and  $\frac{1}{2} (T_F - F)$  are called the positive and negative variations of  $F$ .

**Remark.** We have

$$
\frac {1}{2} (T _ {F} + F) (x) = \sup  \left\{\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {n} \left(F \left(x _ {j}\right) - F \left(x _ {j - 1}\right)\right) ^ {+}: x _ {0} &lt;   \dots &lt;   x _ {n} = x \right\} + \frac {1}{2} F (- \infty),
$$

$$
\frac {1}{2} (T _ {F} - F) (x) = \sup  \left\{\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {n} \left(F (x _ {j}) - F (x _ {j - 1})\right) ^ {-}: x _ {0} &lt;   \dots &lt;   x _ {n} = x \right\} - \frac {1}{2} F (- \infty).
$$

**Proof.** Note

$$
\begin{array}{l} \left(T _ {F} (b) + F (b)\right) - \left(T _ {F} (a) + F (a)\right) = \sup  \left\{\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {n} \left(\left| F (x _ {j}) - F (x _ {j - 1}) \right| + \left(F (x _ {j}) - F (x _ {j - 1})\right)\right): a = x _ {0} &lt;   \dots &lt;   x _ {n} = b \right\} \\ = 2 \sup  \left\{\sum_ {j = 1} ^ {n} \left(F (x _ {j}) - F (x _ {j - 1})\right) ^ {+}: a = x _ {0} &lt;   \dots &lt;   x _ {n} = b \right\}. \\ \end{array}
$$

