Proposition 3.30 If $F \in NBV$, then $F' \in L^1(m)$. Moreover,

$$
\mu_F \perp m \text{ if and only if } F' = 0 \text{ a.e., and}
$$

$$
\mu_F \ll m \text{ if and only if } F(x) = \int_{-\infty}^{x} F'(t) \, dt.
$$

Proof. WLOG, assume that $F$ is real valued. Decompose $\mu_F$ as

$$
d\mu_F = d\lambda + f \, dm.
$$

Apply Theorem 3.22.

