Corollary 3.33 If $f \in L^{1}(m)$, then

$$
F(x) = \int_{-\infty}^{x} f(t) \, dt
$$

is $NBV$ and absolutely continuous.

Conversely, if $F \in NBV$ is absolutely continuous, then

$$
F' \in L^{1}(m) \quad \text{and} \quad F(x) = \int_{-\infty}^{x} F'(t) \, dt.
$$

Proof. Apply Propositions 3.30 and 3.32.

